        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 21 at 2:29PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 228 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Manhattan, or 18 miles northwest of Bozeman, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Church Hill, Bozeman, Belgrade, Menard, Manhattan, and Amsterdam.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
